pageContext.claim: “The cost of health insurance for American families had skyrocketed under Obama and Biden by $4,800.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump's number appears on target but "skyrocketed" is probably the wrong term, as  health-care costs slowed during the eight years of the Obama administration. Under Trump, health insurance premiums increased about $2,500 for a family plan at a large company in his first three years as president.
